<section class="hero">
  <span class="eyebrow">Localhost-only API Security</span>
  <h1>Global Energy Exchange</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    This Express app layers IP filtering, CORS, rate limiting, JWT Bearer auth,
    and Basic Auth to secure the oil price endpoints.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="card-grid">
  <article class="card">
    <h2>1. Generate a JWT</h2>
    <p>Send your username and password to the token endpoint.</p>
    <pre><code>POST /auth/token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "energy-admin",
  "password": "CrudeOil2026!"
}</code></pre>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <h2>2. Call the API</h2>
    <p>Use the returned JWT in the Authorization header.</p>
    <pre><code>GET /api/oil-prices
Authorization: Bearer &lt;your_jwt_token&gt;</code></pre>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <h2>3. Open the Dashboard</h2>
    <p>The dashboard stays on Basic Auth as a second access mode.</p>
    <pre><code>GET /dashboard
Username: energy-admin
Password: CrudeOil2026!</code></pre>
    <p><strong>Important:</strong> the username includes a hyphen and the password is case-sensitive.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="info-panel">
  <div>
    <h2>Security Stack</h2>
    <ul class="plain-list">
      <li>IP Filter: <code>127.0.0.1</code> and <code>::1</code> only</li>
      <li>CORS Origin: {{allowedOrigin}}</li>
      <li>Rate Limit: 10 requests per minute</li>
      <li>API Auth: JWT Bearer token</li>
      <li>Dashboard Auth: HTTP Basic Auth</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="actions">
    <a class="button" href="/dashboard">Open Dashboard</a>
    <a class="button button-secondary" href="/logged-out">View Logout Screen</a>
  </div>
</section>
